# Bear Agents & Skills Index

Use these skills to keep Bear work consistent. Reference by skill name when starting a task.

## Skills (`.cursor/skills/`)

| Skill | When to use |
|-------|-------------|
| **bear-ui-standards** | Creating/refactoring components — types, consts, BEM, translations, file layout, `useBearId` |
| **bear-component-workflow** | Adding a new component or portal page — 4-file pattern, barrel, nav, changelog |
| **bear-js-fundamentals** | Component logic — Promises, event loop, when to avoid `useEffect` / `useCallback` / `useMemo` |
| **bear-code-review** | Structured review — hooks, SVG helpers, props pattern, portal PropsTable, `/bear-code-review` |
| **bear-code-quality** | Code review — types in type files, constants in const files, no magic numbers/strings, logic-first |
| **bear-release-workflow** | Version bumps, CHANGELOG, build, publish |

## How to invoke

- "Follow bear-ui-standards when refactoring Select"
- "Use bear-component-workflow to add ToggleButton"
- "Run /bear-code-review on FormControl"
- "Prepare 1.2.4 per bear-release-workflow"

## Legacy rule

`bear-ui-standards.mdc` is superseded by the **bear-ui-standards** skill. Prefer the skill for full guidance including component IDs.

## Publishing

All ForgeStack packages follow `forge-publishing.mdc` in forgestack — `@forgedevstack/bear`, CI on push to `main`.
